%N A394972 On a graph with points (k, prime(k)), k>=1, consider if prime(n) is on any previously drawn infinite line between prime(j) and prime(j-1), where 2<=j<=n-1. If not, draw an infinite line between prime(n) and prime(n-1). The sequence gives the total number of lines drawn, starting from prime(2).
%C A394972 The sequence overall shows long periods of near linear growth interrupted by short periods of much slower growth, with the later periods getting further apart as n increases. See the attaching images.
%C A394972 In the first 1000000 terms the longest run of equal terms is 294 terms all equal to 8607, from a(16996) to a(17279). This is broken by prime(17280) = 191461, after which there is another run of 252 terms all equal to 8608. There is no other run of equal terms approaching these lengths in the first 1000000 terms, and given this occurs after only 16996 terms, it is plausible this is the longest run of equal terms for all n, although this is unknown.
%C A394972 See A395217 for the primes where a new line is drawn.
%H A394972 Scott R. Shannon, <a href="/A394972/b394972.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 2..10000</a>
%H A394972 Scott R. Shannon, <a href="/A394972/a394972.png">Image of the first 20000 terms</a>. The run of terms a(16996)..a(17279) = 8607 is highlighted in red. The green line is a(n) = n.
%H A394972 Scott R. Shannon, <a href="/A394972/a394972_1.png">Image of the first 1000000 terms</a>.
%e A394972 a(2) = 1 as initially there are no lines drawn, so draw an infinite line between (2,prime(2)) = (2,3) and (1,prime(1)) = (1,2).
%e A394972 a(3) = 2 as the point (3,prime(3)) = (3,5) is not on the one previously drawn line, so draw an infinite line between (3,prime(3)) = (3,5) and (2,prime(2)) = (2,3).
%e A394972 a(4) = 2 as the point (4, prime(4)) = (4,7) is on the line drawn between prime(3) = 5 and prime(2) = 3, so no new line is drawn.
%e A394972 a(10) = 7 as the point (10,prime(10)) = (10,29) is on the line drawn between prime(7) = 17 and prime(6) = 13, so no new line is drawn. This is the second of fifteen consecutive terms equal to 7.
%Y A394972 Cf. A395217 (primes where a new line is drawn), A000040, A373813, A376187.
%K A394972 nonn,new
%O A394972 2,2
